text: hey team - jenna and i just went through the JIRA tickets listed above. were unclear on what is needed for some of these or why they are blocked, so please provide any additional insight / needs in the tickets (comment with <@U0U9WJB7F> so she's sure to get them while we're with kat + can follow up with you ASAP so you get what you need) :slightly_smiling_face:
<@U2670DYLE>
<@U2670DYLE|johncohoon> has joined the channel

<@U2670DYLE> regarding lynsey’s comment in JIRA about push notifications, we’re going to want to add a flag to the push registration endpoint to mark “new world” users so people on modern (non-NFC hardware) will be somehow logically different on the backend and they can be bucketed
(this makes more sense in person)
Is this just a flag that is included in the payload of a push notification?
yes - thank you! john also happy to chat through in person (with client right now but can swing by later) if needed!
mostly wanted to jot it down before we forgot
<@U2670DYLE> no in this case we’d want to make sure that the inbound registration endpoint can capture if the user is “new” or “old” world
then when sending a push, we’d want to be able to say “only send to people with newer cases”
or older
etc.
if that makes sense
Ok, that makes sense. we'll just query when it comes time to send the notification.
yep!

<@U3ZFEAPSP> <@U2H61EJSG> <@U1ZG1UCAK> how are things coming along considering our Wednesday deadline tomorrow? I think the things we're *most* concerned about at this point are the Trends Visualization and the new Earth Images. Would love just a general update on progress/blockers.
Concerning the Trends visualisation, Here is the closest to the supplied image I can provide currently:

Also, I am currently using the existing case colors but I can easily add more color options.
